Prac 7 -
creating , scheduling and building jobs in Jenkins

Sign-in with your credentials or create first admin user
Inside Jenkins > New item > Name-website > Freestyle project > OK
General > description : test reachability of website
Build steps > Add > Execute Windows batch command > paste the following:

@echo off
echo Checking Website health...

curl -ls --connect-timeout 5 --max-time 10 https://google.com >NUL || exit /b 1
curl -ls --connect-timeout 5 --max-time 10 https://github.com >NUL || exit /b 1
curl -ls --connect-timeout 5 --max-time 10 https://jaihindcollege.com >NUL || exit /b 1

echo All sites are up

Next SAVE.
Click on BUILD NOW. (should build successfully.)
Check status

Click on configure and change the college name to misspelling.
curl -ls --connect-timeout 5 --max-time 10 https://jaihindcolleges.com >NUL || exit /b 1

Next SAVE > BUILD NOW > Job should fail.

SCHEDULING JOB:
Configure > Triggers > Build periodically > Schedule > 
25 01 * * 0-7 (FORMAT (M H * * 0-7) 

eg.Run at 2:30 PM every day
30 14 * * *


WITH PYTHON CODE -
New item > python_project (Freestyle project) > OK
Configure > general > Description: to execute python code

Environment > Build steps > Add > Execute Windows batch command > paste the following:

python –version(two hyphen)

SAVE > Next >  build now.

Configure > Build steps > Add > Execute Windows batch command > paste the following:

echo print("Hello Jenkins") > pythontest.py

SAVE. > BUILD NOW > should run successfully > 
Go to workspace > pythontest.py file should appear.
